                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/7–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-08T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 8, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 8—8:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2534. Reference Legation’s telegram 2442, July 3, Legation learns from reliable
                    source that Hjalmer Poehl, mentioned as intermediary between two German SS
                    officials and Legation’s alien radio monitor, is known as one of most important
                    German agents operating in Baltic States and has been operating on behalf of
                    German Intelligence Service during trips between Sweden and Estonia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
